The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as surface normal estimation and single-view depth estimation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses domain adaptation techniques, which fall under cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of anchor tasks, such as semantic segmentation and facial landmarks, suggests a possible connection to graphics and visualization (cs.GR). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed methods on image datasets suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
